UN refugee agency official kidnapped in Mali . An official of the UNHCR United Nations refugee agency has been kidnapped in Mali , a spokesman said on Wednesday . The official was snatched from his home in the northeastern town of Kidal by two unidentified attackers on Sunday evening and taken to an unknown destination , the spokesman said . The agency named the staff member as Martin Bucumi , 41 , a Burundian who was head of UNHCR ' s Kidal office . The motive behind his kidnapping was not known and there were no further details , the UNHCR said . The Geneva - based agency said it was discussing the attack with officials of the West African state . 
